Yes. You can send Javascript to be evaluated by UIAutomation so it has all the capabilities of that UIAutomation does. There&#x27;s a PR that adds this natively <a href="https://github.com/inkling/Subliminal/pull/118" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/inkling/Subliminal/pull/118</a>, but you can also just implement it yourself quite easily:<p><pre><code>    - (void)captureScreenshotWithFilename:(NSString *)filename
    {
        [[SLTerminal sharedTerminal] evalWithFormat:@&quot;UIATarget.localTarget().captureScreenWithName(\&quot;%@\&quot;)&quot;,
                                                [filename slStringByEscapingForJavaScriptLiteral]];
    }</code></pre>
